article.headline: Sam Houston St. 68, Texas St. 52
article.story: HUNTSVILLE, Texas -- Lance Pevehouse scored 25 points and Gilberto Clavell added 13 as Sam Houston State defeated Texas State 68-52 on Saturday night. The Bearkats (15-15, 10-6 Southland) denied the Bobcats (17-12, 10-6) a share of the conference championship. McNeese State won the Southland outright by beating Lamar on Saturday and will be the top need in next week's conference tournament. Sam Houston State is the No. 3 seed in the tournament; Texas State will be the fourth seed. Ryan White had 15 points and 10 rebounds for the Bobcats, and Tony Bishop added 14 points. Pevehouse made 7 of 10 3-point attempts for the Bearkats, who never trailed after the first four minutes.
